The District of Columbia Office of Human Rights (OHR) works to eradicate discrimination, increase equal opportunity, and protect the human rights of individuals who live in, work in, or visit the District of Columbia. In support of this mission, the Data Analyst will be an experienced technologist and subject matter expert in the Data Services field; with a focus on data analysis and data mining. The OHR Data Analyst will be responsible for creating scripts to identify and correct common errors and data inconsistencies in incoming data. The Data Analyst will also design and implement reports using SQL as well as a variety of reporting and business intelligence tools. The successful candidate will perform with minimal oversight and act as a technical lead on data-driven dashboard applications projects.
